    "narrative": "The lineup today is anchored by **Corbin Carroll** (74.01) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92), our clear top-tier options. **Corbin Carroll** benefits from a strong xwOBA (0.372) and a favorable turn in the lineup at #3, while **Vinnie Pasquantino** is poised to feast against the 4.61 xERA of Luis Severino, bolstered by a significant park factor and a 14% boost from dynamic platoon projections. Joining them in the high-efficiency tier is **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.72), who remains an excellent utility play despite the \"Lineup Pending\" tag, thanks to a healthy projection against Michael Wacha. **Josh Naylor** (71.58) also slots in as a high-floor start, capitalizing on the #4 spot to maximize RBI opportunities against Taj Bradley.\n\nOur focus on speed remains critical; while **Brice Turang** (64.04) and **Trevor Story** (61.48) aren't the highest-scoring players, they provide the necessary SB upside. **Trevor Story** specifically receives an 8% lift from BvP history against Lauer, mitigating the risk of his sub-par raw base projection. We are betting on the volatility of the back-end bats: **Kyle Karros** (63.06) is a sneaky play today, elevated by a wind-aided environment and a soft matchup against Williamson (5.40 xERA). Conversely, **Jose Caballero** (41.62) is barely holding onto a start; his abysmal matchup against Eovaldi and the #9 spot makes him our most vulnerable position player today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was leaving **Alex Freeland** (47.61) out of the MI slot. He narrowly missed the cut, primarily hindered by the #9 lineup position, which suppressed his efficiency compared to **Brice Turang**. We opted for **Brice Turang**\u2019s better order placement to capture the run-scoring potential at the top of the lineup. As a final note, we are monitoring the lineups for **Vinnie Pasquantino** and **Tyler Soderstrom** closely, as any deviation from our assumed batting order could force a re-evaluation of our daily caps. We are keeping **Austin Riley** (43.21) sidelined for the time being, as he struggles to offer competitive value against a high-tier arm like Skubal.",
